images.title: Fiesta at Siesta
images.caption: Fiesta at Siesta
images.desc: Here we are in mid-March already, the time of year when college-age revelers invade the world's beaches, like this one on Florida's Siesta Key. Located in Sarasota County off the state's western shore, the island beach is a fixture on lists of America's top beaches, a standout even in a state where soft, welcoming sands compose over half the 1,200-mile coastline.
